One thing I'm wondering though (if we go through with my proposal) is whether we might consider splitting up the giant `types/index.d.ts` into smaller files with static and chain types colocated as we go? I'm finding it pretty hard to navigate as-is, and I think the risk of types between `MathJsStatic` and `MathJsChain` getting out of sync is fairly high.

Something like:

#### **`types/type/bignumber.d.ts`**
```ts
import { Decimal } from 'decimal.js'

declare namespace math {
  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-empty-interface
  interface BigNumber extends Decimal {}

  interface MathJsStatic {
    /**
     * Create a BigNumber, which can store numbers with arbitrary precision.
     * When a matrix is provided, all elements will be converted to
     * BigNumber.
     * @param x Value for the big number, 0 by default.
     * @returns The created bignumber
     */
    bignumber(
      x?: number | string | Fraction | BigNumber | boolean | Fraction | null
    ): BigNumber
    bignumber<T extends MathCollection>(x: T): T
  }

  interface MathJsChain<TValue extends number | string | Fraction | BigNumber | boolean | Fraction | null | MathCollection> {
    /**
     * Create a BigNumber, which can store numbers with arbitrary precision.
     * When a matrix is provided, all elements will be converted to
     * BigNumber.
     */
    bignumber(
      this: MathJsChain<number | string | Fraction | BigNumber | boolean | Fraction | null>,
    ): MathJsChain<BigNumber>
    bignumber<T extends MathCollection>(this: MathJsChain<T>): MathJsChain<T>
  }
}
```

