Make `gamma` generic, so we can write the following code. Typescript won't report any error because it can infer the types of the argument and the returned value.

```ts
// Typescript knows gamma returns number here so using syntax `+` here is ok
const a = mathjs.gamma(123) + mathjs.gamma(456)

// Typescript knows gamma returns BigNumber/Decimal here, so call `add` here is ok
const b = mathjs.gamma(mathjs.bignumber(123)).add(mathjs.gamma(mathjs.bignumber(456)))
```

